    <stitle>AIR COMPRESSOR: BENDIX TU-FLO 501 - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>When any component is serviced or removed from the air system, be sure to set the parking brake
                    and block the vehicle wheels to prevent it from moving while service is being performed.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drain air pressure from all reservoirs.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drain engine cooling system and cylinder head of compressor.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect all air, water and oil lines leading to and from the compressor.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove compressor mounting bolts and drive belts as required.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove compressor from engine.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use suitable puller to remove pulley or gear from compressor crankshaft after removing
                crankshaft nut.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect pulley or gear and related parts for wear or damage. If any parts are found worn or
                damaged, they must be replaced.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
